  When you sign up for an account you designate your email address.  This email address is not shared with anyone.  However, if it's associated with a [Gravatar](https://en.gravatar.com) account (yours, of course!) it will designate your avatar.  If you don't have one, please create one.

  One easy way to do specify an alternate image without having to create a new email address is to [use a plus address](https://www.wikihow.com/Use-Plus-Addressing-in-Gmail).

  If your gmail account is `jrrtolkien@gmail.com`, for example, you can designate alternate identities using plus accounts such as `jrrtolkien+frodo@gmail.com` and `jrrtolkien+samwise@gmail.com`.  Doing so bypasses the need to create new email addresses to associate with new avatars.  A single Gravatar account can be associated with several email addresses and/or plus addresses.  Choose your email address accordingly and configure Gravatar with whatever image you like.

  Once you've linked your email address to an image on Gravatar, [edit your profile here](/profiles/edit).  Make a small change and submit it.  Every time you update your profile, your avatar is updated from Gravatar.  If your email address was correctly linked to your Gravatar account, your avatar will appear.
